# VS Code REST Client / compatible tools
# Start server with mock mode (PowerShell):
#   $env:API_V1_MOCK_MODE="true"
#   uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000 --reload

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000

### 0 — Check mock mode & sample IDs
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/mock/info

### 0b — Reset mock data to defaults
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/mock/reset

### 1 — Upload (mock project MOCK-001)
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/upload
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----mock

------mock
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="projectId"

MOCK-001
------mock
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

source_documents
------mock
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="test.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

%PDF-1.4 mock file content
------mock--

### 2 — Autosave
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/autosave
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "projectId": "MOCK-001",
  "reportType": "trf",
  "section": "section-1",
  "data": { "field1": "hello", "field2": 42 }
}

### 3 — Report dashboard (all mock projects)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/report-dashboard?user_role=1

### 3b — Report dashboard (user filter)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/report-dashboard?user_role=2&user_email=mock.user@intertek.test

### 3c — Single project
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/report-dashboard?project_id=MOCK-001

### 4 — KPI dashboard
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/kpi-dashboard?user_role=1

### 5 — Report statistics
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/report-statistics?user_role=1
